<DOC><DOCNO> AP880811-0105 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-11-88 1218EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r p PM-Reagan-Bush 1stLd-Writethru a0571 08-11 0174</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Reagan-Bush, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0571,150</SECOND><HEAD>Reagan, Bush, To Meet Briefly In Transit At GOP Convention</HEAD><NOTE>EDS: Adds 2 grafs on Bush arrival.</NOTE><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   President Reagan and Vice President GeorgeBush are expected to meet briefly while they are in the New Orleansarea for the Republican National Convention next week, the WhiteHouse said today.   Presidential spokesman Marlin Fitzwater said tentative planscalled for the president and the prospective GOP presidentialcandidate to meet on Tuesday at Belle Chase Naval Air Station.   The vice president will be arriving in New Orleans that day andthe president will be leaving for California, where he willvacation at his ranch north of Santa Babarara and in Los Angeles.   Fitzwater said Reagan and Bush planned to discuss thetentatively scheduled meeting during a lunch with their wives todayin the Oval Office.   Bush, arriving for the lunch, told reporters, ``We're going totalk about how to win.''   Asked whether he and Reagan would meet during the convention, hesaid, ``We'll talk about that also.''</TEXT></DOC>